@Havick007
It is not illegal to download or upload files in the US.  

When you purchase music or a movie, what you are purchasing is a "License Agreement" which is a special contract.  Your purchase is consideration which enters you into this contractual obligation.  In the "License Agreement" you agree not to distribute copies to others.  If you set up a disk burning operation and sell them, then you are committing fraud which is illegal because you are knowingly making a profit from someone else's intellectual property.

If they could bust people for downloading then they would do it.  The music industry is run by foul soulless creatures.  They want paid everytime that you sing Happy Birthday to someone.  The only people that they go after are the people who do not know their rights (like you).  They just want to get a few example cases out there to make people believe that they have the upperhand but the bottom line is if people understood what they are doing, their business would be ruined.

Thank God for Piratebay and others who know how to fight them.
